The simplest way to run a test is:

  $ csem --pcabs --pail --pcore --skip-core-tcheck --std $CSEM/model/core_std/std.core --execute filename

this will:
  * pretty-print the cabs, ail and core representations
  * skip the core typechecking which is out of date currently
  * run the core program

The script run.sh does all this without the --execute

If there is a crash or loop, the option --debug shows a "real time"
detailed trace.
